    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "If the hole is near a shed or foundation, does that suggest groundhog?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Often yes. Groundhogs frequently burrow along foundations, under sheds, porches, slabs, or at the base of trees. Moles are usually traveling under turf and gardens and don’t create a large den entrance you can step into."
